data.name: Aaron Bright
data.headline: Business Development at Galileo Financial Technologies
data.summary:
I spend my days helping companies reimagine how money moves. At Galileo Financial Technologies, I lead B2B sales, working with banks, fintechs, and brands to build new payment solutions. What really excites me is exploring what’s next in fintech—whether that’s how businesses embed financial tools, how stablecoins and real-time payments shift the landscape, or how we make financial services more useful for people every day.

Before Galileo, I learned the ropes at Meta Payment Systems (Pathward Bank) and U.S. Bank, where I partnered with fintechs to bring new card and payment programs to life.

If you’re curious about the future of payments, want to swap ideas about where the industry is headed, or just enjoy a good conversation about building what’s next, I’m always up for it.

data.name: Aaron Cheiffetz
data.headline: Executive Strategist | Field CIO at CDW
data.summary: Aaron Cheiffetz serves as an Executive Strategist and Field CIO for The Financial Services Industry. Mr. Cheiffetz is responsible for leading transformation road mapping, IT Economics and enterprise-wide program execution. He partners with clients to identify fit for purpose technologies and implement strategies that drive measurable results to align with desired outcomes. Before joining CDW he was a Hybrid Cloud & AI platform consultant at IBM focused on financial services clients.  Earlier in his career he held a variety of roles at AT&T in consulting, technical sales and integrated technology go-to-market strategy. He holds an MBA in Corporate Strategy and Finance from Wake Forest University School of Business.
